ith $C_{2}H_{2}F_{4}$ and its low GWP (around 7). Preliminary tests with\ncosmic rays have shown promising results in terms of detector performance. The\nnext step is to study the long-term behavior of RPCs operated with these new\ngas mixtures (aging studies). Since this is a subject of interest for all (and\nnot only) the LHC experiments, a collaboration, ECOgas@GIF++, was setup to\ncarry out joint studies. Among others, a small ALICE-like RPC was installed at\nthe Gamma Irradiation Facility at CERN, where they are exposed to a strong\nradiation field, coming from a 12.5 TBq $^{137}$Cs source, which allows one to\nsimulate many years of operation in a relatively short time. The facility also\nprovides a muon beam at specific times of the year, which can be used to study\nthe detector performance (e.g. efficiency and cluster size) during and after\nirradiation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 5 Sep 2022 15:41:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-09-07"}
